inet.ipaddr

Interface IPAddressAggregation<T extends IPAddress,R extends IPAddressSeqRange>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    R -
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IPAddressCollection<T,R>, IPAddressRange
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IPAddress, IPAddressContainmentTrie, IPAddressContainmentTrieBase, IPAddressSeqRange, IPAddressSeqRangeList, IPv4Address, IPv4AddressContainmentTrie, IPv4AddressSeqRange, IPv4AddressSeqRangeList, IPv6Address, IPv6AddressContainmentTrie, IPv6AddressSeqRange, IPv6AddressSeqRangeList

    public interface IPAddressAggregation<T extends IPAddress,R extends IPAddressSeqRange>
    An IPAddressAggregation represents an object instance that can represent an aggregation, a multitude, of individual addresses.

    Types implementing this interface include IPAddress which represents either individual addresses or subnets, IPAddressSeqRange which represents sequential ranges, and the sub-interface IPAddressCollection which represents collections of IP addresses. IP address collection implementations includes IPAddressSeqRangeList, a collection backed backed by sequential ranges, and IPAddressContainmentTrie, a collection backed by tries of CIDR prefix blocks.

      • isSequential

        boolean isSequential()
        Returns whether the addresses in this aggregation are sequential.

        An aggregation is sequential if, given any two addresses in the aggregation, any address between the two is also in the aggregation. If the aggregation has no addresses, it satisfies this condition. In other words, an empty aggregation is sequential.

        Returns:

      • coverWithSequentialRange

        IPAddressSeqRange coverWithSequentialRange()
        Returns the unique sequential range of minimal size that includes all the addresses in this aggregation. If there are no addresses in this aggregation, then null is returned.

        The result will represent the same set of addresses if and only if the set of addresses in this aggregation are sequential, in which isSequential() is true.

      • coverWithPrefixBlock

        IPAddress coverWithPrefixBlock()
        Returns the unique CIDR prefix block subnet or individual address of minimal size that includes all the addresses in this aggregation. If there are no addresses in this aggregation, then null is returned.
